SymptomDescription: You were weak and fell to the ground.
Your body started moving suddenly and you could not control it.

SymptomName: Blurry vision, Sudden vision loss, or numbness on side of body/limb
SymptomDescription:
You suddenly could not see, or
You suddenly had no feeling in your arm, leg, or on one side of your face or body.

SymptomName: Severe chest discomfort or chest pain
SymptomDescription: You felt a lot of pain/ tightness in your chest that you could not explain.
You felt your heart much beating faster than normal.

SymptomName: Shortness of breath with usual activities
SymptomDescription: You have a hard time breathing when doing everyday activities, e.g. when walking short distances.
You felt dizzy, weak, or faint when you stood up.
Your tongue or lips looked or felt larger than usual, e.g. reaction to new medication.
You notice you have lost weight without trying to.

SymptomName: Significant hunger or weakness to point of shaking
SymptomDescription: You felt so hungry or weak such that your body shook or trembled.
You felt very tired, with no energy to do anything.
You felt like urinating very often or were very thirsty.

SymptomName: Slow healing or infected foot wound
SymptomDescription: You have a wound on your foot that is not healing.

SymptomName: Foot numbness, tingling, and/ or pain
SymptomDescription: You lost feeling in your foot, or you feel prickly, burning, or pain in your foot.
